 "Teachers should keep the following in mind when using this iDevice: <ol><li>Think about the number of different types of activity planned for your resource that will be visually signalled in the content. Avoid using too many different types or classification of activities otherwise learner may become confused. Usually three or four different types are more than adequate for a teaching resource.<\/li><li>From a visual design perspective, avoid having two iDevices immediately following each other without any text in between. If this is required, rather collapse two questions or events into one iDevice. <\/li><li>Think about activities where the perceived benefit of doing the activity outweighs the time and effort it will take to complete the activity. <\/li><\/ol>": "U\u010ditelji morajo imeti v mislih, kadar uporabljajo pou\u010devalne enote, naslednje:<ol><li>\u0160tevilu razli\u010dnih vrst dejavnosti, na\u010drtovanih za vir, ki bodo ozna\u010dene v vsebini. Izogibati se je treba preveliki uporabi razli\u010dnih vrst dejavnosti, saj lahko prevelika raznolikost zmede u\u010dence. Obi\u010dajno so dovolj tri ali \u0161tiri razli\u010dne vrste ve\u010d kot primerne za u\u010dni vir.<\/li><li>Iz oblikovnega stali\u0161\u010da, se izognite uporabi dveh pou\u010devalnih enot, ki si sledita takoj ena za drugo brez vmesnega besedila. V primeru, da je taka zasnova naloge, je bolje zdru\u017eiti dve vpra\u0161anji ali dva dogodka v eno pou\u010devalno enoto.<\/li><li>3.Kak\u0161no je razmerje med dejavnostjo in \u010dasom \u010das ter naporom dolo\u010denim za re\u0161evanje naloge.<\/li><\/ol>", 
